INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A solutions architect wants to configure an Amazon Bedrock model so that it stops generating text whenever it produces the string '###END###' in its output. Which inference parameter controls this behavior?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"temperature"},{"id":"b","text":"top_p"},{"id":"c","text":"max_tokens"},{"id":"d","text":"stop_sequences"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["d"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$According to the source material, 'stop_sequences' is listed as a common inference parameter. Stop sequences are strings that signal the model to cease generation when encountered, making them the correct control for halting output at a specific token pattern like '###END###'. temperature controls randomness, top_p performs nucleus sampling to limit the probability mass considered, and max_tokens sets a hard upper limit on output length — none of these trigger stopping at a specific string.$patch$, $patch$Fundamentals of Generative AI$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/bedrock/latest/userguide/inference-parameters.html","label":"Amazon Bedrock Inference Parameters"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'AIF-C01-P1'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A solutions architect wants to configure an Amazon Bedrock model so that it stops generating text whenever it produces the string '###END###' in its output. Which inference parameter controls this behavior?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A developer is building a complex generative AI workflow in Amazon Bedrock that must autonomously call external APIs, retrieve data, and complete multi-step tasks with minimal human intervention. Which Bedrock feature is purpose-built for this orchestration pattern?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Knowledge Bases for Amazon Bedrock"},{"id":"b","text":"Agents for Amazon Bedrock"},{"id":"c","text":"Model Evaluation"},{"id":"d","text":"Bedrock Guardrails"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material explicitly states that 'Agents for Amazon Bedrock — orchestrate multi-step tasks calling tools/APIs,' which directly matches the requirement for autonomous, multi-step API orchestration. Knowledge Bases handle document ingestion and retrieval for RAG. Model Evaluation compares foundation models on performance metrics. Bedrock Guardrails enforce safety policies — none of these provide the orchestration runtime for calling external APIs and chaining steps.$patch$, $patch$Fundamentals of Generative AI$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/bedrock/latest/userguide/agents.html","label":"Agents for Amazon Bedrock"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
