INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A data science team needs a foundation model deployment on Amazon Bedrock that guarantees consistent, low-latency inference throughput for a production workload with predictable traffic. Which Bedrock feature addresses this need?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Knowledge Bases for Amazon Bedrock"},{"id":"b","text":"Bedrock Guardrails"},{"id":"c","text":"Provisioned Throughput"},{"id":"d","text":"Model Evaluation"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material states 'Provisioned Throughput — reserved capacity for predictable latency,' which directly addresses the need for consistent, low-latency inference under predictable production traffic. Knowledge Bases manage document ingestion for RAG workflows. Bedrock Guardrails configure safety filters. Model Evaluation benchmarks model quality — none of these reserve compute capacity to guarantee throughput or latency.$patch$, $patch$Fundamentals of Generative AI$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/bedrock/latest/userguide/prov-throughput.html","label":"Provisioned Throughput – Amazon Bedrock"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
