INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$Under the AWS shared responsibility model as it applies to Amazon Bedrock, which of the following is an AWS responsibility rather than a customer responsibility?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Configuring IAM policies to restrict which users can invoke foundation models"},{"id":"b","text":"Enabling and reviewing Bedrock model invocation logs"},{"id":"c","text":"Protecting the physical infrastructure and hardware that runs the Bedrock service"},{"id":"d","text":"Applying Bedrock Guardrails to filter sensitive content in prompts"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The Bedrock security documentation states: 'Security OF the cloud: AWS protects the infrastructure that runs AWS services. Third-party auditors regularly test and verify effectiveness as part of the AWS Compliance Programs.' Physical infrastructure protection is therefore an AWS responsibility. All other options — configuring IAM policies, enabling invocation logging, and applying Guardrails — fall under 'Security IN the cloud,' which is the customer's responsibility based on their data sensitivity, company requirements, and applicable regulations.$patch$, $patch$Security, Compliance, and Governance for AI$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/bedrock/latest/userguide/security.html","label":"Amazon Bedrock Security – Shared Responsibility Model"},{"url":"https://aws.amazon.com/compliance/shared-responsibility-model/","label":"AWS Shared Responsibility Model"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
